CARD ID: 0
CANONICAL TSA NAME (always use this name in the reading): The One
RWS EQUIVALENT (reference only; do not name it in the reading): The Fool
ELEMENT: Air

NAMING RULE:
- In all writing outputs, call this card "The One" (never call it "The Fool").
- You may use traditional "Fool" symbolism internally, but the public-facing name must remain "The One".

CORE MEANING (UPRIGHT SUMMARY):
- A new beginning.
- The first step of a journey.
- Faith in your path, even before the map appears.
- Openness, willingness, curiosity, and brave innocence.

UPRIGHT (ALI BIRD VOICE):
Any journey begins with a step. Tangible roads place one foot in front of the other, yet the spiritual path often begins with an idea, a feeling, a whim. With you as The One, your wandering will has lit the torch to your dreams and now there is nothing that can anchor you to stay. Mind that the cover of nightfall is aided by moonlight. Your inner knowing will illuminate the motivations guiding your way.

REVERSED (SUMMARY):
- Reluctance or hesitation to begin.
- Waffling, second-guessing, weighing risks until momentum disappears.
- Fear of looking foolish; fear of making the “wrong” first move.

REVERSED (ALI BIRD VOICE):
When The One appears reversed, the journey is still calling — but you may be bargaining with the beginning. This can look like waiting for perfect certainty, asking for extra signs, or trying to eliminate every risk before you move. If your heart is quietly leaning forward, trust the smallest next step. You don’t need the whole plan. You only need enough courage to begin.

WHEN THIS CARD SHOWS UP:
- You’re at the edge of something new (a choice, identity shift, relationship chapter, move, project, practice).
- Your intuition is louder than your logic right now.
- The lesson is not “be fearless” — it’s “be willing.”

PRACTICAL GUIDANCE:
- Choose the smallest real-world step (one email, one application, one conversation, one morning ritual).
- Trade perfection for momentum: start imperfectly, then refine.
- If nervous system fear is high, move gently: slow courage still counts.

KEYWORDS / TAGS:
- beginning, leap of faith, innocence, openness, adventure, intuition-led, first step, curiosity

ALIAS / SEARCH HELP (for retrieval only):
- The Fool, Fool archetype, new journey, leap, beginner, trust the path

CARD ID: 1
CANONICAL TSA NAME (always use this name in the reading): The Enchanter
RWS EQUIVALENT (reference only; do not name it in the reading): The Magician
ELEMENT: Air

NAMING RULE:
- In all writing outputs, call this card "The Enchanter" (never call it "The Magician").
- You may use traditional Magician symbolism internally, but the public-facing name must remain "The Enchanter".

CORE MEANING (UPRIGHT SUMMARY):
- Personal power and resourcefulness.
- Inner genius and capability becoming visible.
- Turning intention into action; translating desire into something real.
- Abundance in aptitude: you already have what you need to begin.

UPRIGHT (ALI BIRD VOICE):
Sparks. Tears. Soil. Whispers. An ace of each with an incantation of willpower will raise your desires from the depths of The Universe. The Enchanter may show you the tools, but you were in possession of them from the moment your journey began. What revelation will stir you to realize that every quality you possess is a hidden talent, skill, or secret gift? Which, if given the opportunity to flourish, will assist your dreams and result in manifestations beyond your wildest expectation.

REVERSED (SUMMARY):
- Dormant abilities; underestimating your power.
- Feeling unprepared or “not ready yet.”
- Becoming hoodwinked: distraction, self-doubt, or outside influence dimming your confidence.

REVERSED (ALI BIRD VOICE):
When The Enchanter appears reversed, it can feel like the tools are just out of reach — but more often, they’re already in your hands and you don’t believe you’re allowed to use them. This is a call to reclaim your capability. Beware of shiny distractions, borrowed opinions, or inner narratives that insist you must wait. Your magic doesn’t arrive later. It strengthens when you practice it now.

WHEN THIS CARD SHOWS UP:
- You’re ready to start, create, pitch, apply, build, or initiate.
- The path forward asks for confidence + follow-through.
- The lesson is to trust your skill and choose focused action.

PRACTICAL GUIDANCE:
- Name the “tools on your table” (skills, connections, resources, time windows).
- Choose one intention and take one concrete step within 24–72 hours.
- Reduce distractions: focus beats force.

KEYWORDS / TAGS:
- willpower, resourcefulness, capability, initiation, manifestation, focus, inner genius, tools, intention

ALIAS / SEARCH HELP (for retrieval only):
- The Magician, manifestation, skill, will, focused creation, personal power

CARD ID: 2
CANONICAL TSA NAME (always use this name in the reading): The Enchantress
RWS EQUIVALENT (reference only; do not name it in the reading): The High Priestess
ELEMENT: Water

NAMING RULE:
- In all writing outputs, call this card "The Enchantress" (never call it "The High Priestess").
- You may use traditional High Priestess symbolism internally, but the public-facing name must remain "The Enchantress".

CORE MEANING (UPRIGHT SUMMARY):
- Inner knowing and intuitive clarity.
- Secrets revealed through stillness.
- Trusting what you sense before you can prove it.
- Wisdom without force: guidance that doesn’t dictate.

UPRIGHT (ALI BIRD VOICE):
Within the silence, you will finally be able to hear. The voice of our own knowing is a whisper in our psyche. The voice of our desires? A wail. The Enchantress will offer wisdom, but is wise enough to omit a direction. If we constantly look to others for this (even to those as exalted as The Enchantress herself) we will forever be lost along the paths they lead us towards and not the path we know to be true. The words of your inner wisdom will come to you in whispers. Be careful not to speak over its message.

REVERSED (SUMMARY):
- Ignoring the inner voice; outsourcing your certainty.
- Being led astray by noise, opinions, or validation-seeking.
- Confusing desire, anxiety, or fantasy for true intuition.

REVERSED (ALI BIRD VOICE):
When The Enchantress appears reversed, the message is still there — but something is drowning it out. This can look like asking everyone what you should do, scrolling for reassurance, or forcing an answer before it’s ready. Your intuition doesn’t shout; it repeats. Create a small pocket of quiet and ask one clean question. Then listen for the whisper that returns again and again.

WHEN THIS CARD SHOWS UP:
- You already know more than you’re admitting.
- Clarity comes through stillness, not pressure.
- The next step is to trust your internal compass and reduce outside noise.

PRACTICAL GUIDANCE:
- Take 10 minutes of silence (no phone, no input) and ask: “What do I know to be true?”
- Write the first 3 sentences that arrive without editing.
- If you’re seeking validation, pause and ask: “What am I afraid will happen if I trust myself?”

KEYWORDS / TAGS:
- intuition, inner knowing, mystery, stillness, discernment, sacred wisdom, quiet truth, secrets

ALIAS / SEARCH HELP (for retrieval only):
- High Priestess, psychic insight, inner voice, discernment, mystery, feminine wisdom

CARD ID: 3
CANONICAL TSA NAME (always use this name in the reading): The Great Mother
RWS EQUIVALENT (reference only; do not name it in the reading): The Empress
ELEMENT: Earth

NAMING RULE:
- In all writing outputs, call this card "The Great Mother" (never call it "The Empress").
- You may use traditional Empress symbolism internally, but the public-facing name must remain "The Great Mother".

CORE MEANING (UPRIGHT SUMMARY):
- Creation, nourishment, and patient growth.
- Cycles of nature: timing, ripening, and sustainable abundance.
- Devotion to what you are building (ideas, relationships, home, body, projects).
- Fertility in the broad sense: what wants to grow through you.

UPRIGHT (ALI BIRD VOICE):
The Great Mother rules over the astrological year. She knows the cycles of the sun and moon and uses them to her advantage when planning the growth of her kingdom. As she walks with you through her bountiful orchards she tells you that gardens are much like ideas. Too little water and your seed will never sprout. Too much, and your seed will rot before its leaves taste sunlight. Adjusting to the needs of the ideas you nurture will yield the greatest outcome. Oh, and be patient. All seeds planted take time to grow.

REVERSED (SUMMARY):
- Smothering or over-nurturing; giving too much, too fast.
- Domestic upheaval or imbalance in care, comfort, and responsibility.
- Wrath at loss: grief, disappointment, or resentment when things don’t grow as hoped.

REVERSED (ALI BIRD VOICE):
When The Great Mother appears reversed, the question becomes: where has care turned into control? You may be watering the seed out of fear — checking, pushing, over-giving, trying to guarantee the outcome. Or you may be depleted from carrying too much of the emotional or domestic load. This is a call to rebalance the tending: nourish what is yours to nurture, and let the rest breathe. Growth is natural — but it cannot be rushed.

WHEN THIS CARD SHOWS UP:
- Something is ready to be nurtured into form: a relationship, home life, creative work, or self-care rhythm.
- Timing matters. Your pace is part of the magic.
- The lesson is sustainable devotion, not intensity.

PRACTICAL GUIDANCE:
- Choose one “seed” to nourish consistently this week (a habit, a project, a relationship ritual).
- Ask: “What’s the right amount of water?” (effort, attention, time) — then do that, not more.
- Create a container for patience: a weekly check-in instead of daily pressure.

KEYWORDS / TAGS:
- nurture, abundance, fertility, creation, patience, cycles, embodiment, home, devotion, growth

ALIAS / SEARCH HELP (for retrieval only):
- The Empress, mother archetype, creation, harvest, sensuality, nature cycles, fertility

CARD ID: 4
CANONICAL TSA NAME (always use this name in the reading): The Great Father
RWS EQUIVALENT (reference only; do not name it in the reading): The Emperor
ELEMENT: Fire

NAMING RULE:
- In all writing outputs, call this card "The Great Father" (never call it "The Emperor").
- You may use traditional Emperor symbolism internally, but the public-facing name must remain "The Great Father".

CORE MEANING (UPRIGHT SUMMARY):
- Leadership, structure, and integrity.
- Fair rule: boundaries, responsibility, and decisions with consequences.
- Building and protecting what matters through order and discipline.
- Authority earned through character, not control.

UPRIGHT (ALI BIRD VOICE):
He who rules, must reign. To do so fairly, justly, and with honor was never a question for The Great Father. Law and Order are the principles guiding his kingdom to greatness. The Great Father teaches that how you choose to lead speaks volumes of your character. On the moral spectrum, where would you land? Choose wisely, for your capacity for greatness hinges on the quality of your empire.

REVERSED (SUMMARY):
- Tyranny or excessive control; forcing outcomes.
- Rigidity, domination, or harshness (toward self or others).
- “Time to abdicate”: releasing a role, identity, or power dynamic that is no longer aligned.

REVERSED (ALI BIRD VOICE):
When The Great Father appears reversed, leadership may be turning into control. This can look like gripping too tightly, demanding certainty, or trying to manage people and outcomes beyond your reach. Or it can show up as the opposite: avoiding responsibility and letting the “empire” run itself into chaos. The invitation is to return to clean authority — boundaries with kindness, decisions with integrity, and structure that supports life rather than restricts it.

WHEN THIS CARD SHOWS UP:
- You are being asked to lead: your life, your work, your home, your choices.
- A boundary is required for stability.
- The lesson is disciplined integrity: consistent actions that match your values.

PRACTICAL GUIDANCE:
- Define one clear boundary and enforce it calmly.
- Make one “empire-quality” decision: choose what supports the long-term, not just the moment.
- Ask: “Am I leading from integrity — or from fear?”

KEYWORDS / TAGS:
- leadership, boundaries, structure, integrity, authority, discipline, protection, order, responsibility

ALIAS / SEARCH HELP (for retrieval only):
- The Emperor, ruler archetype, structure, sovereignty, law, order, leadership

CARD ID: 5
CANONICAL TSA NAME (always use this name in the reading): The Sage
RWS EQUIVALENT (reference only; do not name it in the reading): The Hierophant
ELEMENT: Earth

NAMING RULE:
- In all writing outputs, call this card "The Sage" (never call it "The Hierophant").
- You may use traditional Hierophant symbolism internally, but the public-facing name must remain "The Sage".

CORE MEANING (UPRIGHT SUMMARY):
- Wisdom earned through experience and tradition.
- Learning, teaching, mentorship, and ceremony.
- Turning the past into guidance for future action.
- Legacy: passing knowledge forward with integrity.

UPRIGHT (ALI BIRD VOICE):
Come into Ceremony. Close your eyes and be. When your thoughts drift to fears, how do you navigate the treacherous waves that follow? What holds power over you, has no power at all when you do not fear its loss. Learning to take your past and translate it into lessons for future action is a valuable skill. The Sage encourages you to create a legacy from the experiences and knowledge you’ve gained. He passes you a scroll. It’s time to start writing.

REVERSED (SUMMARY):
- Blindly following; borrowing beliefs that don’t fit.
- Independence over community: isolating when guidance would help.
- Power trips: gatekeeping, rigidity, or “I know best” dynamics.

REVERSED (ALI BIRD VOICE):
When The Sage appears reversed, the question is whether wisdom is guiding you — or rules are. This can be the moment you realize a belief, tradition, or authority no longer fits your life. Or it can be a warning about spiritual or social power being misused: someone (including you) insisting on certainty instead of curiosity. Choose discernment. Honor what is true, keep what is helpful, and release what requires you to abandon yourself.

WHEN THIS CARD SHOWS UP:
- You’re being asked to learn, study, practice, or commit to a path.
- A mentor, structure, or community could support you.
- The lesson is translating lived experience into wisdom you can apply.

PRACTICAL GUIDANCE:
- Choose one practice you can return to consistently (daily, weekly, or seasonal).
- Ask: “What lesson from my past can guide my next decision?”
- Seek wise counsel — but keep your inner authority.

KEYWORDS / TAGS:
- ceremony, tradition, mentorship, learning, teaching, legacy, wisdom, community, practice

ALIAS / SEARCH HELP (for retrieval only):
- The Hierophant, teacher archetype, tradition, institution, spiritual practice, mentorship

CARD ID: 6
CANONICAL TSA NAME (always use this name in the reading): The Beloved
RWS EQUIVALENT (reference only; do not name it in the reading): The Lovers
ELEMENT: Air

NAMING RULE:
- In all writing outputs, call this card "The Beloved" (never call it "The Lovers").
- You may use traditional Lovers symbolism internally, but the public-facing name must remain "The Beloved".

CORE MEANING (UPRIGHT SUMMARY):
- Desire, attraction, and meaningful choice.
- Following what calls you — with discernment.
- A turning point: choosing alignment over convenience.
- Affection beyond romance (people, paths, projects, values).

UPRIGHT (ALI BIRD VOICE):
That which pulls at your attention, and claims your desire is The Beloved. If a person, place, item, idea is darling to you then it has declared its place on your path. The Beloved is intended to be chased, though the catch may be elusive. The choice is yours to allow such magnetism to sway you from your trajectory, knowing that it may lead you on an unfruitful detour. Should the fruit be yours to taste, however, you will not bite into a sweeter reward.

REVERSED (SUMMARY):
- Elusive obtainment; hoops to jump through.
- Dependency, attachment, or chasing what does not choose you back.
- Confusion between desire and alignment; temptation without integrity.

REVERSED (ALI BIRD VOICE):
When The Beloved appears reversed, desire may be leading the mind more than the soul. This can look like chasing, bargaining, over-investing, or trying to earn what should be freely offered. It can also show up as attachment to an idea that once felt sweet, but no longer nourishes you. The invitation is to choose with integrity: let desire be a signal, then ask if the path is mutual, sustainable, and aligned with your values.

WHEN THIS CARD SHOWS UP:
- A choice is asking to be made (in love, work, identity, or direction).
- You are being pulled by something magnetic — and discernment is required.
- The lesson is alignment: choosing what matches your values, not just your craving.

PRACTICAL GUIDANCE:
- Ask: “Is this desire leading me toward myself — or away from myself?”
- Choose one value (honesty, stability, growth, peace) and use it as your compass.
- If this is about a person: look for reciprocity, not intensity.

KEYWORDS / TAGS:
- desire, choice, alignment, attraction, values, devotion, reciprocity, temptation, turning point

ALIAS / SEARCH HELP (for retrieval only):
- The Lovers, partnership, choice, values alignment, temptation, devotion

CARD ID: 7
CANONICAL TSA NAME (always use this name in the reading): The Marionette
RWS EQUIVALENT (reference only; do not name it in the reading): The Chariot
ELEMENT: Water

NAMING RULE:
- In all writing outputs, call this card "The Marionette" (never call it "The Chariot").
- You may use traditional Chariot symbolism internally, but the public-facing name must remain "The Marionette".

CORE MEANING (UPRIGHT SUMMARY):
- Taking command of your direction.
- Willpower and coordinated movement.
- Maintaining control of many moving parts.
- Action despite uncertainty; steering your life with intention.

UPRIGHT (ALI BIRD VOICE):
Like The Marionette, your every movement tugs at the cosmic cords of The Fates. When every cause is accompanied by an equal yet unknowable effect, it can feel challenging to risk action against obscurity. The Marionette asks you to take command as the puppetmaster of your life and put on the show of your destiny. By orchestrating the cosmic cords, you now have control. Be calculated in your flourishes, for The Fates are still in audience.

REVERSED (SUMMARY):
- Tripping up; lack of coordination.
- Paralysis: too many variables, not enough traction.
- Unfavourable cascades: small missteps causing outsized consequences.

REVERSED (ALI BIRD VOICE):
When The Marionette appears reversed, the cords may feel tangled. You might be trying to steer too many moving parts at once, or waiting for certainty that won’t arrive. This is a call to simplify the show: choose one clear direction, set one steady rhythm, and release what you cannot control. Momentum returns when your actions become consistent, not frantic.

WHEN THIS CARD SHOWS UP:
- You’re being asked to choose a direction and commit.
- Coordination matters: timing, planning, follow-through.
- The lesson is disciplined movement: steering your life instead of being pulled by circumstance.

PRACTICAL GUIDANCE:
- Name the destination: “What am I moving toward?”
- Pick one next step that is measurable and time-bound.
- Reduce variables: delegate, postpone, or drop one moving part.

KEYWORDS / TAGS:
- direction, willpower, momentum, control, coordination, commitment, disciplined action, steering, destiny

ALIAS / SEARCH HELP (for retrieval only):
- The Chariot, willpower, victory through discipline, forward motion, self-mastery

CARD ID: 8
CANONICAL TSA NAME (always use this name in the reading): Lady Leo
RWS EQUIVALENT (reference only; do not name it in the reading): Strength
ELEMENT: Fire

NAMING RULE:
- In all writing outputs, call this card "Lady Leo" (never call it "Strength").
- You may use traditional Strength symbolism internally, but the public-facing name must remain "Lady Leo".

CORE MEANING (UPRIGHT SUMMARY):
- Confidence and courage.
- Gentle power: calm mastery over fear and impulse.
- Steadfast devotion to what matters.
- Turning self-doubt into forward movement.

UPRIGHT (ALI BIRD VOICE):
Radiating self assurity, Lady Leo can tame any fear, can domesticate any distress. She moves innocently, yet gracefully in the pursuit of her passions, and encourages you to do the same. There is no room for hesitation in the manifestation journey with Lady Leo on your side. With gentle strength and steadfast courage, any shortfall can be overcome. May your whispers become roars as you claim your place as a force in this great universe.

REVERSED (SUMMARY):
- Doubting your potential; shrinking back.
- Insecurities manifesting as defensiveness, hostility, or self-sabotage.
- Tactlessness: power expressed without tenderness.

REVERSED (ALI BIRD VOICE):
When Lady Leo appears reversed, courage may be available — but self-doubt is interrupting the signal. This can look like playing small, over-explaining, or protecting yourself with sharpness instead of softness. The medicine is steady gentleness: speak to yourself like someone you love, take one brave step anyway, and let confidence be built through action rather than waiting for it to arrive fully formed.

WHEN THIS CARD SHOWS UP:
- You are being asked to act from courage instead of fear.
- Confidence is built by doing, not by perfect certainty.
- The lesson is soft power: firm boundaries with an open heart.

PRACTICAL GUIDANCE:
- Choose one “roar”: one brave act you can do today (send the message, make the ask, begin the work).
- Practice self-respect in small ways (posture, rest, honest words).
- If fear spikes, slow down — then proceed gently, not dramatically.

KEYWORDS / TAGS:
- confidence, courage, gentle power, self-trust, bravery, devotion, steadiness, heart-led action

ALIAS / SEARCH HELP (for retrieval only):
- Strength card, lion energy, courage, calm power, resilience, heart

CARD ID: 9
CANONICAL TSA NAME (always use this name in the reading): The Pearl
RWS EQUIVALENT (reference only; do not name it in the reading): The Hermit
ELEMENT: Earth

NAMING RULE:
- In all writing outputs, call this card "The Pearl" (never call it "The Hermit").
- You may use traditional Hermit symbolism internally, but the public-facing name must remain "The Pearl".

CORE MEANING (UPRIGHT SUMMARY):
- Introspection, solitude, and inner guidance.
- Wisdom formed in quiet; preparing to shine.
- Seeking truth beneath surface noise.
- Refinement: becoming through stillness and patience.

UPRIGHT (ALI BIRD VOICE):
Brilliance is the reward of introspection. The Pearl lies protected in it’s clamshell, dumb to the ongoings of the ocean. As it is gaining its glistening layers, The Pearl is surrounded by calm, tranquillity, and an occasional caress of the current of inspiration. Go within. Tune the world out. Search for the gems lurking in the depths of your personal trenches. When you are finally exposed to the world, the promise is that you will shine.

REVERSED (SUMMARY):
- Withdrawal or isolation to a detriment.
- Avoiding connection, support, or reality.
- Irritation at disruption; protecting your quiet by shutting down.

REVERSED (ALI BIRD VOICE):
When The Pearl appears reversed, solitude may have turned into hiding. The shell that once protected your brilliance can become a wall that keeps nourishment out. This is a gentle reminder: introspection is meant to serve your life, not replace it. Let yourself receive one safe connection, one honest conversation, or one grounded step back into the world — even if it’s small. Your shine doesn’t diminish when seen; it strengthens.

WHEN THIS CARD SHOWS UP:
- You need space to think, integrate, and listen to yourself.
- The answer comes from within, not from rushing outward.
- The lesson is quiet devotion: time alone used wisely.

PRACTICAL GUIDANCE:
- Create a “stillness window” (10–30 minutes) with no input, then journal what rises.
- Ask one clean question: “What truth am I ready to admit?”
- If you’ve been isolating, choose one gentle reconnection (text a trusted person, book support, step outside).

KEYWORDS / TAGS:
- introspection, solitude, inner wisdom, refinement, quiet truth, integration, guidance, preparation

ALIAS / SEARCH HELP (for retrieval only):
- The Hermit, inner light, solitude, contemplation, searching within, wisdom

CARD ID: 10
CANONICAL TSA NAME (always use this name in the reading): The Fates
RWS EQUIVALENT (reference only; do not name it in the reading): Wheel of Fortune
ELEMENT: Fire

NAMING RULE:
- In all writing outputs, call this card "The Fates" (never call it "Wheel of Fortune").
- You may use traditional Wheel symbolism internally, but the public-facing name must remain "The Fates".

CORE MEANING (UPRIGHT SUMMARY):
- Turning points and timing.
- Karma, cause-and-effect, and the momentum of choices.
- A cusp of positive change; life shifting into a new cycle.
- Aligning actions now to influence what arrives next.

UPRIGHT (ALI BIRD VOICE):
Luck, is for The Fates. 
Tied by golden cosmic cords, all our actions and interactions are accounted for. To do a good deed is to cause our cords to glow. The Fates in turn reward the brightest of networks with abundance beyond measure, however their delivery often comes on the cusp of change. Do not fear the turn of Fate. If flowing is desired, the glowing must be acquired. Choose your next steps with care.

REVERSED (SUMMARY):
- Repercussions of poor behaviour; consequences catching up.
- Feeling the universe is working against you.
- A reminder to recalibrate: choices, patterns, and integrity matter.

REVERSED (ALI BIRD VOICE):
When The Fates appears reversed, it can feel like the wheel is turning the “wrong” way — but often it’s simply revealing the true cost of misalignment. This isn’t punishment; it’s information. Something in the pattern needs to be corrected. Return to clean choices. Repair what you can, release what you can’t, and let your next steps be guided by integrity. The glow can be rebuilt, one decision at a time.

WHEN THIS CARD SHOWS UP:
- A shift is underway: timing is active, and momentum is real.
- A cycle is ending and another is beginning.
- The lesson is to move with change instead of fighting it.

PRACTICAL GUIDANCE:
- Ask: “What pattern is repeating — and what choice breaks it?”
- Make one integrity-based decision today (even a small one).
- Stay flexible: prepare, but don’t cling to one outcome.

KEYWORDS / TAGS:
- timing, turning point, karma, cycles, fate, momentum, change, alignment, cause-and-effect

ALIAS / SEARCH HELP (for retrieval only):
- Wheel of Fortune, destiny, cycles, luck, turning point, karmic change, timing

CARD ID: 11
CANONICAL TSA NAME (always use this name in the reading): The Scales
RWS EQUIVALENT (reference only; do not name it in the reading): Justice
ELEMENT: Air

NAMING RULE:
- In all writing outputs, call this card "The Scales" (never call it "Justice").
- You may use traditional Justice symbolism internally, but the public-facing name must remain "The Scales".

CORE MEANING (UPRIGHT SUMMARY):
- Truth, fairness, and consequence.
- Balance restored through honest accounting.
- Integrity: alignment between actions, values, and outcomes.
- Decisions made with clarity, not emotion or manipulation.

UPRIGHT (ALI BIRD VOICE):
Fair must remain fair or else The Scales will tip. When equality veers into injustice, we can expect an adjustment to bring The Scales back into balance. Rewards and consequences will be dealt in logical hands, and no act of bribery or manipulation can change the outcome. What is fair may not be what is desired, but it ensures that no accumulation of abundance leaves the other bowl bereft.

REVERSED (SUMMARY):
- The gravity of grievances; resentment building.
- Inequity left uncorrected; imbalance tolerated too long.
- Unfavourable favouritism; unclear standards or biased dynamics.

REVERSED (ALI BIRD VOICE):
When The Scales appears reversed, something feels uneven — and your spirit knows it. This can be a sign that boundaries are too soft, expectations are unclear, or fairness has been postponed in the name of keeping peace. It can also point to distorted standards: judging yourself harshly while excusing others, or accepting crumbs where you deserve equity. The invitation is to correct the imbalance with clean honesty. Name what is true, then choose what is fair.

WHEN THIS CARD SHOWS UP:
- A decision is required — one that respects truth and consequence.
- You are being asked to act with integrity, even if it’s uncomfortable.
- The lesson is fairness: clear standards, honest boundaries, and equal exchange.

PRACTICAL GUIDANCE:
- Ask: “Where is the exchange uneven — time, effort, care, money, respect?”
- Make one boundary or request that restores balance.
- Choose clarity over persuasion: state facts, not just feelings.

KEYWORDS / TAGS:
- fairness, truth, balance, integrity, accountability, consequence, boundaries, clear standards

ALIAS / SEARCH HELP (for retrieval only):
- Justice card, fairness, legal matters, accountability, truth, balance restored

CARD ID: 12
CANONICAL TSA NAME (always use this name in the reading): The Mime
RWS EQUIVALENT (reference only; do not name it in the reading): The Hanged Man
ELEMENT: Water

NAMING RULE:
- In all writing outputs, call this card "The Mime" (never call it "The Hanged Man").
- You may use traditional Hanged Man symbolism internally, but the public-facing name must remain "The Mime".

CORE MEANING (UPRIGHT SUMMARY):
- A conscious pause that creates a new perspective.
- Sacrifice that awakens growth.
- Stepping back to propel forward.
- Commitment to the practice: refining your message, your path, your purpose.

UPRIGHT (ALI BIRD VOICE):
Manifestation is often aided with a commitment to the practice. The Mime may have surrendered their voice, but has gained so much more in their depth of expression. The Mime's mute displays put them in the spotlight and encourage a crowd, which they may never have achieved without this choice along their path. What do you dare to lose to propel you into your dreams? When you finally return to your voice, how much more might you have to say?

REVERSED (SUMMARY):
- Unnecessary standstill; delay without purpose.

POSITION KEY: advice
POSITION NAME: Advice

Meaning:
- The most supportive next step you can take.
- The action, boundary, conversation, or mindset that reduces friction.

How to interpret:
- Make the advice doable in real life. Prefer one clear step over many.

Tone rules:
- Encourage self-respect, clarity, and emotional safety.

POSITION KEY: block
POSITION NAME: Block

Meaning:
- The main friction point slowing progress (internal or external).
- A constraint, fear, pattern, belief, or practical obstacle.
- What must be acknowledged honestly (without shame) to move forward.

How to interpret:
- Name the block clearly.
- Distinguish between:
  - internal blocks (fear, avoidance, perfectionism, old stories)
  - external blocks (time, money, logistics, other people’s limits)

Tone rules:
- Blocks are information, not failure.
- Avoid blame and avoid catastrophizing.

POSITION KEY: bridge
POSITION NAME: Bridge

Meaning:
- The most supportive next step that reduces the block.
- A concrete action, system, boundary, or support that makes progress easier.
- The bridge is doable within your current life and capacity.

How to interpret:
- Give 1 practical step that can be taken in the next 24–72 hours.
- If relevant, suggest a support structure (schedule, accountability, help from others).

Tone rules:
- Prefer simple, sustainable actions over dramatic leaps.
- Momentum matters more than intensity.

POSITION KEY: focus
POSITION NAME: Focus

Meaning:
- The highest-impact priority right now.
- What to center your attention on so things simplify.

How to interpret:
- Identify the core theme beneath distractions.

Tone rules:
- Keep it clear and direct.

POSITION KEY: future
POSITION NAME: Future

Meaning:
- The likely direction if nothing changes (not fate).
- The next growth edge.
- What becomes more likely as you keep walking this path.

How to interpret:
- Name the pattern and offer a steering action that can improve the outcome.

Tone rules:
- Never speak in absolutes. Use “may,” “tends to,” and “if you choose.”

POSITION KEY: goal
POSITION NAME: Goal

Meaning:
- What you’re truly aiming for (the deeper desire beneath the surface).
- The most aligned version of the outcome.
- What success looks like in a way that fits your values and capacity.

How to interpret:
- Name the “real goal,” not just the surface want.
- Clarify what the goal requires (commitment, time, courage, skill, support).

Tone rules:
- Encourage clarity and self-honesty.
- Avoid pressure or perfectionism.

POSITION KEY: hidden_issues

Tone rules:

SPREAD KEY: fml
SPREAD NAME: Focus • Moving Forward • Letting Go

Purpose:
- A directional spread that clarifies what to prioritize now, how to take the next step with momentum,
  and what to release so progress feels lighter and more aligned.

Positions:
1) Focus
- What deserves your attention right now (the highest-impact priority).
- The core theme that will make the biggest difference if you work with it.
- The “anchor point” that steadies you.

2) Moving Forward
- The next best step: how to progress with clarity and momentum.
- A practical action, mindset shift, conversation, or support to pursue.
- What builds trust in yourself through consistent movement.

3) Letting Go
- What is draining you, distracting you, or keeping you stuck.
- A pattern, belief, attachment, expectation, or habit that can be released.
- What becomes easier when you stop carrying this.

Rules:
- Keep it actionable: translate each position into one real-life step.
- Letting go is not “giving up” — it’s releasing what isn’t aligned or isn’t yours to hold.
- Offer agency: “If you choose X, you may experience Y.”
- End with 1–3 concrete next actions + one journal prompt.

SPREAD KEY: gsbbl
SPREAD NAME: Goal · Status · Block · Bridge · Lesson

Purpose:
- A forward-moving spread that turns a desire into a grounded plan:
  what you want, where you are, what’s in the way, what helps you cross it, and what you’re learning.

Positions:
1) Goal
- What you’re truly aiming for (the deeper desire beneath the surface).
- The most aligned version of the outcome.
- What success looks like in a way that fits your values and capacity.

2) Status
- The current reality: what’s happening now and what resources you actually have.
- What is already working (or trying to work).
- The “truth on the ground” so the plan is realistic.

3) Block
- The main friction point slowing progress (internal or external).
- A constraint, fear, pattern, belief, or practical obstacle.
- What needs to be acknowledged honestly (without shame) to move forward.

4) Bridge
- The most supportive next step that reduces the block.
- A concrete action, system, boundary, or support that makes progress easier.
- The “bridge” is practical and doable within your current life.

5) Lesson
- What this goal is teaching you about yourself.
- The growth edge you’re building (patience, courage, discernment, discipline, trust, etc.).
- How to integrate the learning so the progress becomes sustainable.

Rules:
- Keep it practical: turn insight into 1–3 next actions.
- Avoid moralizing. Blocks are information, not failure.
- Offer agency: “If you do X, you make Y more likely.”
- End with a short plan (next step + one supportive habit) and one journal prompt.
